1
00:00:00,933 --> 00:00:02,133
<i>I don't know anything
about Hotel 88.</i>

2
00:00:02,133 --> 00:00:04,233
<i>Don't worry.
You'll work with someone.</i>

3
00:00:04,233 --> 00:00:05,500
<i> Who?</i>

4
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:07,567
<i>Are you sure we're getting
Edward to promote the hotel?</i>

5
00:00:07,567 --> 00:00:10,033
<i>We need Edward
so I can execute my plan</i>

6
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:12,367
<i>of kicking the brothers
out of Hotel 88.</i>

7
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:15,433
<i>Finders keepers, remember?
So, it should be mine.</i>

8
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:17,067
<i>Give it to me
if you don't like it.</i>

9
00:00:17,067 --> 00:00:19,433
<i>I'll see if I like it.
But I'm gonna keep this.</i>

10
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:21,367
<i> There's a gun but no papers.</i>

11
00:00:21,367 --> 00:00:22,300
<i> Just a gun?</i>

12
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:24,567
<i>Why? Should there be
something else?</i>

13
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,267
<i> It's my deposit.</i>

14
00:00:26,267 --> 00:00:28,700
<i>I know it's not all of it,
but I'll still pay you back.</i>

15
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>- We need to talk.
- About what?</i>

16
00:00:31,567 --> 00:00:32,967
<i> Where's the guest's money?</i>

17
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,067
Yeah, I took it.

18
00:00:43,567 --> 00:00:45,500
Return the money
before the guest gets back!

19
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:47,033
That's enough!

20
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:49,467
What if word gets out
that there's a thief in here?

21
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:52,333
Please, stop it. Calm down.

22
00:00:54,367 --> 00:00:56,367
Are you out of your mind, Gio?

23
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:59,000
Did you even read the fine print
on the partnership agreement?

24
00:00:59,633 --> 00:01:00,600
[SCOFFS]

25
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:02,200
Obviously, not!

26
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,533
It's written on there
in black and white!

27
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:07,333
"If any of the partners engage
in activities

28
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:11,233
that compromise the hotel's
reputation or operations,

29
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:14,100
the other family will take away
our management authority!"

30
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:15,133
That's enough!

31
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:16,700
Please.

32
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:18,600
Enough? No, Kiko.

33
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:21,200
He needs to understand this.

34
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,567
Because one mistake...

35
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,033
is all it takes.

36
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:27,233
You know how they think.

37
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:30,400
Legally, they will take this all
away from us.

38
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:33,233
Stop being so selfish.

39
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:36,100
Then, I'm selfish!

40
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,400
I'd rather die being selfish,

41
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,200
than put my grandma's life
at risk!

42
00:01:41,533 --> 00:01:45,300
You have the money to pay off
people who threaten your family.

43
00:01:46,233 --> 00:01:47,267
But me...

44
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:50,233
I have nothing.

45
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:54,467
If I don't pay them back,

46
00:01:55,367 --> 00:01:57,133
they'd come back for Mommyla.

47
00:01:57,767 --> 00:02:00,767
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

48
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,800
She's my only family, Martin.

49
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:05,500
I can't lose her.

50
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:10,233
So, you used the money
to pay off your debts?

51
00:02:12,133 --> 00:02:13,100
Not yet.

52
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:15,400
I was thinking about it.

53
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:16,633
But it's all here.

54
00:02:17,567 --> 00:02:18,767
I didn't use it at all!

55
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:22,300
There you go!

56
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,433
Choke yourself with it!

57
00:02:27,367 --> 00:02:28,767
I don't care what you think.

58
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:33,400
But I won't commit a crime
just to save my grandma's life.

59
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:50,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:12,767
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

61
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:34,767
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

62
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:44,767
Luna.

63
00:03:45,733 --> 00:03:48,267
Yes, I'm here.
I'm waiting for Edward.

64
00:03:49,667 --> 00:03:51,333
Okay. Bye.

65
00:03:52,967 --> 00:03:53,933
[SIGHS]

66
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,833
Excuse me?

67
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:01,500
Have you told Edward
that I'm here?

68
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:03,733
I've been waiting here
for 30 minutes.

69
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,333
Yes, ma'am.
He's almost done at the gym.

70
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:07,533
He asks you to wait for him.

71
00:04:07,767 --> 00:04:09,300
Seriously?

72
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:12,467
He knows what time I'm coming
and he went to the gym?

73
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:18,800
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYS]

74
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:34,800
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:04:39,433 --> 00:04:41,333
Did you really sell it?

76
00:04:43,567 --> 00:04:45,533
I got around 600,000 out of it.

77
00:04:46,667 --> 00:04:48,900
How did you even
get that deep in debt?

78
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,867
You worked so hard for that car,

79
00:04:50,867 --> 00:04:52,967
and you just used it
to pay off a debt?

80
00:04:52,967 --> 00:04:55,333
Well, I got this left.

81
00:04:55,533 --> 00:04:56,467
See?

82
00:04:58,667 --> 00:04:59,633
Gio...

83
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:04,433
Don't worry, Mommyla.

84
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:06,500
I can save up for another one.

85
00:05:06,867 --> 00:05:09,633
I just made sure that Bok
won't come back for you.

86
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:11,600
[SIGHS] Okay.

87
00:05:12,633 --> 00:05:13,767
I love you, dear.

88
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:16,467
- I love, love, love you.
- Love you.

89
00:05:17,033 --> 00:05:19,633
It's just a car. Mm-mm.

90
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:21,400
Next time, I'll buy two.

91
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:35,567
Excuse me?

92
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,933
Is Edward ready yet?

93
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:40,867
- Oh, there he is.
- Sorry.

94
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:44,700
Why?

95
00:05:44,967 --> 00:05:46,533
Sorry for being late?

96
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:47,967
[SNORTS]

97
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:50,467
Sorry, I didn't get to dress up.

98
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:52,800
[SCOFFS] So arrogant...

99
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,033
Whatev-- Let's just go.

100
00:05:57,700 --> 00:06:01,667
Has Luna told you that you'll
tour me around Hotel 88?

101
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,667
I need to see and experience it

102
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:08,567
before I could
promote your hotel.

103
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:11,733
I don't just post stuff that...

104
00:06:12,867 --> 00:06:13,867
[CHUCKLES]

105
00:06:16,767 --> 00:06:18,700
...you know, I don't like.

106
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,633
Yes, yes, I know that.

107
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:23,033
Can we just get this over with?

108
00:06:23,033 --> 00:06:24,433
Gosh.

109
00:06:26,033 --> 00:06:28,033
Okay, but we need to go
somewhere first.

110
00:06:28,733 --> 00:06:29,733
Where?

111
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:31,667
Come on. Just follow me.

112
00:06:32,533 --> 00:06:35,500
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYS]

113
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:36,767
[EDWARD] Jade!

114
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:41,467
[KIKO] Gio.

115
00:06:45,567 --> 00:06:47,667
Here, I'll give you 5,000.

116
00:06:47,933 --> 00:06:49,633
No, Kiko. Keep it.

117
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:51,867
Come on, it's yours.

118
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:54,500
It's for Mommyla, not you.

119
00:06:55,167 --> 00:06:56,367
[SCOFFS]

120
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:01,867
And tell that person

121
00:07:01,867 --> 00:07:03,833
that I won't
just give them 5,000.

122
00:07:04,533 --> 00:07:06,433
I can give them 1,000
every month.

123
00:07:07,633 --> 00:07:09,533
Sure, if you want us both
to get beaten up.

124
00:07:09,733 --> 00:07:11,567
No, but seriously,
I can give you more.

125
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:13,900
And where will you
get the money?

126
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,667
I don't know.

127
00:07:17,467 --> 00:07:20,433
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

128
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:22,733
Tell me.

129
00:07:22,967 --> 00:07:24,967
Where did the debt
actually come from?

130
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:28,867
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

131
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:32,533
Aside from selling condos,

132
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,400
I have other side jobs.

133
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:36,900
I buy and sell cars.

134
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:40,633
I got a sports car.

135
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,533
It was a handsome one.

136
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,000
As sleek as it gets.

137
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,033
It's all set up and everything.

138
00:07:50,167 --> 00:07:51,533
They wanted me to sell it.

139
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,200
And that's when
my bad luck started.

140
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:58,633
So, what happened?

141
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:01,800
It got stolen.

142
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:07,167
Didn't you report it?

143
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:10,833
I did.

144
00:08:11,467 --> 00:08:14,067
But you know it's not that easy.

145
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:16,467
They never found it.

146
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,900
And so...

147
00:08:22,133 --> 00:08:25,167
That person wants you
to pay it back?

148
00:08:25,933 --> 00:08:26,900
Yeah.

149
00:08:29,867 --> 00:08:31,667
Exactly that.

150
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,667
But where the hell
would I get 2 million?

151
00:08:38,033 --> 00:08:40,467
Even if I work
all kinds of jobs,

152
00:08:42,633 --> 00:08:44,000
I'd never have that much money.

153
00:08:46,033 --> 00:08:52,967
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

154
00:09:00,933 --> 00:09:03,333
If you're hungry,

155
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:05,233
there's a restaurant
in Hotel 88.

156
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,200
I want to eat here.

157
00:09:07,567 --> 00:09:08,467
It's okay.

158
00:09:08,467 --> 00:09:09,933
We still have
a lot of time, right?

159
00:09:09,933 --> 00:09:12,533
But that doesn't mean
we should waste it.

160
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,333
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

161
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:21,533
I'll make sure not
to waste your time, Jade.

162
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:28,433
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

163
00:09:28,467 --> 00:09:30,667
- Welcome back, sir.
- Hi!

164
00:09:31,267 --> 00:09:34,733
One buttered salmon,
garden salad,

165
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:36,500
and iced americano, please.

166
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,700
What about you, Jade?

167
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,767
Order anything you want.

168
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:42,967
No.

169
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,833
No? Not even coffee,
drinks? Anything?

170
00:09:46,633 --> 00:09:48,333
I want to go back to Hotel 88.

171
00:09:49,767 --> 00:09:51,367
One vegetarian quesadilla.

172
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:53,667
It's good.

173
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,400
Any additional, sir?

174
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,800
That's all. Thank you.

175
00:09:59,367 --> 00:10:02,800
Do you know that our classmate,
Abigail, owns this place?

176
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:06,900
Anyway...

177
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:11,400
Do you remember
when she laughed at me

178
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:14,567
because I couldn't tie
my own shoes?

179
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,467
She said it was because
of my chubby tummy.

180
00:10:20,467 --> 00:10:21,633
Well, guess what?

181
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,800
She approached me
a few years ago

182
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,900
to ask for business advice
for this place.

183
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,800
She couldn't recognize me
at all.

184
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:37,367
She couldn't believe that
the kid she used to bully...

185
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,533
is very different now.

186
00:10:44,633 --> 00:10:45,700
You're right.

187
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:48,967
- You're different now.
- [CHUCKLES]

188
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:51,967
I know, right?

189
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:55,433
[PHONE CHIMES]

190
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,367
[LUNA] How are you and Edward?

191
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:07,700
[JADE CLEARS THROAT]

192
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,300
Wait, where are you going?

193
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:10,733
Ah. To the restroom.

194
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:12,667
Wanna tag along?

195
00:11:13,567 --> 00:11:14,667
[SNORTS]

196
00:11:15,567 --> 00:11:17,767
Why would I come with you
to the restroom?

197
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:24,700
[CHILL MUSIC PLAYING]

198
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:50,333
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

199
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:06,600
[SIGHS] Do we really
have to search here?

200
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,100
It's better to be sure.

201
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:09,900
We might catch someone
doing something suspicious.

202
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:15,600
I'm going to the communities
with CCTV cameras.

203
00:12:15,633 --> 00:12:16,700
Along the direction Jeff took.

204
00:12:17,433 --> 00:12:18,633
The guest of Hotel 88.

205
00:12:18,633 --> 00:12:19,833
Okay.

206
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:23,600
It's good to know where he went
aside from the hotel.

207
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:25,900
Jeff has a criminal record.

208
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:27,633
He has charges
for theft and assault.

209
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:29,833
I'm pretty sure
he's gone into hiding now.

210
00:12:31,133 --> 00:12:33,433
What's important is for us
to find out where he is.

211
00:12:34,133 --> 00:12:35,467
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

212
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:45,933
She's been gone for 30 minutes.

213
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:54,100
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

214
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:58,733
Sir, do you need anything?

215
00:12:58,733 --> 00:13:01,433
No. I'm just gonna check in
with my friend.

216
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:02,833
The girl you came in with?

217
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,867
She already left.

218
00:13:05,533 --> 00:13:07,000
No, she just went
to the restroom.

219
00:13:07,933 --> 00:13:10,567
The toilet upstairs
isn't working, sir.

220
00:13:10,567 --> 00:13:11,833
But the one here on the side
is okay.

221
00:13:13,133 --> 00:13:14,600
Are you sure she left?

222
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,567
She left me?

223
00:13:17,067 --> 00:13:18,200
[WAITRESS] Yes, sir.

224
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:23,900
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:13:23,933 --> 00:13:24,867
Yes, ma'am. I was the one

226
00:13:24,867 --> 00:13:26,067
you were talking to
about the earrings

227
00:13:26,067 --> 00:13:27,733
I already have you check it.

228
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:30,967
Okay. I'm on my way there.

229
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,100
You deserve to be
left alone in that cafe.

230
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:36,967
Gosh, you're so arrogant!

231
00:13:36,967 --> 00:13:37,933
[HUFFS]

232
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,000
Let's earn some money today.

233
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:41,967
[SCREAMS]

234
00:13:41,967 --> 00:13:43,533
[MOTORCYCLE ENGINE REVVING,
HORN HONKS]

235
00:13:43,533 --> 00:13:44,533
[screams]

236
00:13:48,467 --> 00:13:49,200
Ow!

237
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:52,867
[GRUNTS] Aah.

238
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:55,700
- Ow!
- Aah!

239
00:13:58,067 --> 00:13:59,000
- Ow.
- Ah!

240
00:13:59,867 --> 00:14:00,867
[GRUNTS]

241
00:14:02,233 --> 00:14:03,333
Are you okay?

242
00:14:05,733 --> 00:14:06,867
[KIKO GRUNTS]

243
00:14:08,767 --> 00:14:09,967
Does it hurt anywhere?

244
00:14:10,667 --> 00:14:11,733
You again?!

245
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:12,700
[GRUNTS]

246
00:14:13,233 --> 00:14:14,967
Are you my stalker?!

247
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:16,900
Stalker?!

248
00:14:19,767 --> 00:14:20,700
[KIKO] Aah.

249
00:14:22,233 --> 00:14:23,267
[JADE] Ow.

250
00:14:23,267 --> 00:14:24,633
Oh, shocks.

251
00:14:25,667 --> 00:14:26,067
[GRUNTS]

252
00:14:27,167 --> 00:14:28,800
Are you okay?

253
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:30,133
Does it hurt anywhere?

254
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:31,200
Don't touch me.

255
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,300
[EARRING CLINKS]

256
00:14:35,367 --> 00:14:36,633
It's still okay.

257
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:40,367
My god! You almost
broke my earring!

258
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:43,233
If it has a scratch,
its value will depreciate.

259
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:44,900
What are you so mad about?

260
00:14:54,267 --> 00:14:55,367
I know that earring.

261
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:16,667
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

262
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:38,667
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

263
00:15:39,367 --> 00:15:40,867
I have a bad feeling about this.

264
00:15:40,867 --> 00:15:47,800
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:15:52,867 --> 00:15:54,100
Why do you have this?

266
00:15:55,333 --> 00:15:57,333
- I saw it--
- This is ours!

267
00:15:57,333 --> 00:15:59,067
There are only a few of them
in the Philippines,

268
00:15:59,067 --> 00:16:00,100
and that's ours!

269
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:01,767
Are you really sure?

270
00:16:02,733 --> 00:16:05,167
Why? Did you go to the area
where our fathers died?

271
00:16:06,967 --> 00:16:08,233
That's where I found it.

272
00:16:08,267 --> 00:16:10,700
I went to the area
where our fathers died.

273
00:16:12,133 --> 00:16:15,000
Don't tell me you went there
and left that by accident?

274
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,033
[JADE] Wow. I...

275
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:20,867
<i> This looks so nice, Dad.</i>

276
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:24,333
<i> Is it for your anniversary?</i>

277
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,033
<i> Yes.</i>

278
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:34,167
<i> There are only a few of them
in the Philippines.</i>

279
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,067
<i> So I want your mom</i>

280
00:16:38,067 --> 00:16:39,367
<i> to have one, too.</i>

281
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:47,000
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

282
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,733
Hey! Jade, that's mine!

283
00:16:59,633 --> 00:17:00,733
[KIKO] Hey!

284
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:02,567
Hey, that's enough!

285
00:17:02,567 --> 00:17:05,667
- What's your problem?
- Oh...

286
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:08,000
I think he thought
we were fighting.

287
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,233
I'm sorry, sorry.

288
00:17:09,233 --> 00:17:11,433
I saw you kind of
hitting each other, so...

289
00:17:11,433 --> 00:17:13,333
We're good.

290
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:15,300
Martin was actually helping me.

291
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:16,433
It's all good now, okay?

292
00:17:16,433 --> 00:17:18,467
I already called the bank
so they can assist you

293
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:20,633
when you cash the check.

294
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:22,367
Thank you so much, Martin.

295
00:17:22,367 --> 00:17:25,700
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING,
THEN FADES]

296
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:36,100
[LUNA] I was thinking,
we should involve everyone.

297
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:38,400
[FRIDA]
Leon and Justin too.

298
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,767
[LUNA]
Yeah, both of them.

299
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:41,433
[CHUCKLES]

300
00:17:41,433 --> 00:17:42,733
Oh, there she is.

301
00:17:42,733 --> 00:17:44,900
Jade, come here.
Perfect timing.

302
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:47,433
- Can you help us?
- Join us.

303
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:53,500
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:55,900
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

305
00:17:55,900 --> 00:18:02,767
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

306
00:18:04,633 --> 00:18:07,733
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

307
00:18:14,567 --> 00:18:15,933
Mom?

308
00:18:15,933 --> 00:18:16,800
Uh...

309
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,833
Did you ask Jade
to go to your room?

310
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,700
Why?

311
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:23,800
I saw her go in there.

312
00:18:26,933 --> 00:18:29,133
Is something wrong?

313
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:30,900
Nothing, sweetheart.

314
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:33,767
I'll check on her.
Just keep going.

315
00:18:33,767 --> 00:18:39,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

316
00:18:41,067 --> 00:18:42,533
Nice, Gio!

317
00:18:42,533 --> 00:18:44,000
At least
you've got money now.

318
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,567
Your grandma won't be
bothered anymore.

319
00:18:46,567 --> 00:18:48,400
Sorry I couldn't help you.

320
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:50,933
I was going to pawn some
earrings, but they went missing.

321
00:18:50,933 --> 00:18:52,000
You have expensive earrings?

322
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:52,833
- You're joking.
- Where?

323
00:18:52,833 --> 00:18:55,767
No, not mine.
I just found them.

324
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:59,167
I was walking by the beach,
near where Papa died.

325
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,800
Oh?
Where are they now?

326
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:06,567
Well...

327
00:19:06,567 --> 00:19:08,767
Jade suddenly took them.

328
00:19:08,767 --> 00:19:11,633
She said those belonged to them.

329
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:13,833
She said she was sure.

330
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,600
You know,
I was actually wondering

331
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:17,100
why she looked so shocked.

332
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:20,500
Scared?

333
00:19:22,667 --> 00:19:24,533
Kind of.

334
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,100
It's like
they're hiding something.

335
00:19:30,933 --> 00:19:33,033
But if those were theirs,
does that mean...

336
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:36,633
they went there?

337
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:37,767
I don't know.

338
00:19:38,733 --> 00:19:41,067
But weren't we together
that day?

339
00:19:41,067 --> 00:19:42,667
We all went together

340
00:19:42,667 --> 00:19:45,100
when the police said
something bad happened.

341
00:19:47,133 --> 00:19:49,467
But whose are they?

342
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:51,567
Jade's? Luna's?

343
00:19:51,567 --> 00:19:53,167
Or their mom's?

344
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:54,333
I don't know.

345
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:56,767
All Jade told me was
that they're theirs.

346
00:19:58,867 --> 00:20:02,900
I don't know, but I think
we should tell the police.

347
00:20:02,933 --> 00:20:08,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

348
00:20:09,033 --> 00:20:13,700
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

349
00:20:22,933 --> 00:20:26,633
[MUSIC BECOMES TENDER]

350
00:20:26,633 --> 00:20:28,633
[BREATH QUIVERS]

351
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:35,533
[TENDER MUSIC CONTINUES]

352
00:20:42,933 --> 00:20:47,000
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

353
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:51,133
A month before Dad died.

354
00:20:51,133 --> 00:20:53,200
You were already
planning to leave us?

355
00:20:54,267 --> 00:20:56,267
[FRIDA]
It's not what you think.

356
00:20:56,267 --> 00:21:03,133
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

357
00:21:04,533 --> 00:21:05,933
But this?

358
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:09,633
This...

359
00:21:09,667 --> 00:21:12,033
[JADE SOBBING SOFTLY]

360
00:21:12,033 --> 00:21:15,800
You were applying
for residency in Spain!

361
00:21:16,933 --> 00:21:18,267
What is this?!

362
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:23,000
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

363
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:27,567
You did all this
before Dad died?!

364
00:21:27,567 --> 00:21:29,667
You planned all of this?!

365
00:21:30,733 --> 00:21:33,633
Jade, no.
It wasn't like that.

366
00:21:33,633 --> 00:21:36,100
Mom, please tell me the truth.

367
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:39,100
I have so many questions!

368
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:41,633
I feel like I'm going crazy
thinking about it!

369
00:21:41,667 --> 00:21:43,633
Were you going to leave Dad?

370
00:21:43,633 --> 00:21:45,167
Were you going to leave us?

371
00:21:45,167 --> 00:21:47,700
Were you going to go with
Uncle Mike?!

372
00:21:47,700 --> 00:21:48,967
No, sweetheart.

373
00:21:50,033 --> 00:21:51,200
Mike has nothing
to do with this--

374
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:54,033
I know about the affair, Mom!

375
00:21:54,033 --> 00:22:00,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

376
00:22:06,467 --> 00:22:08,267
No, what are you saying?

377
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:09,467
Jade...

378
00:22:10,167 --> 00:22:12,900
- What--
- [JADE] But I kept it a secret.

379
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:18,167
I kept it a secret,

380
00:22:18,167 --> 00:22:21,867
and I didn't tell
any of my siblings.

381
00:22:23,067 --> 00:22:24,933
[SOBBING]

382
00:22:25,367 --> 00:22:26,833
I was angry.

383
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:27,833
Yes!

384
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:31,600
But I wanted to protect you

385
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,400
because I don't want my siblings

386
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:35,333
to look at you
in a different way.

387
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,067
Why?

388
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:41,433
Because they love you so much.

389
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,200
Dear...

390
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:46,067
Jade.

391
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:49,267
That's not the only thing
you've kept from me, Mom.

392
00:22:51,233 --> 00:22:53,200
[SNIFFLING]

393
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:59,933
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

394
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:01,333
[JADE SOBS]

395
00:23:04,367 --> 00:23:05,567
The other pair...

396
00:23:06,867 --> 00:23:07,867
Where is it?

397
00:23:08,133 --> 00:23:09,500
I don't know...

398
00:23:09,500 --> 00:23:11,100
- Where?
- I... I misplaced it.

399
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:12,133
[JADE] Where is it?!

400
00:23:12,133 --> 00:23:13,467
I don't know.

401
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:14,433
Where is it?

402
00:23:17,367 --> 00:23:18,100
Is this it?

403
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,267
It is, right?

404
00:23:23,367 --> 00:23:24,467
It's this, right?!

405
00:23:25,333 --> 00:23:26,267
Yes...

406
00:23:27,933 --> 00:23:29,633
You didn't misplace it, Mom.

407
00:23:31,533 --> 00:23:35,300
You left it near the area
where Dad died.

408
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,167
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

409
00:23:41,367 --> 00:23:43,000
[JADE] Why were you there?

410
00:23:44,333 --> 00:23:46,033
What were you doing there, Ma?

411
00:23:46,033 --> 00:23:48,900
When we went to Hotel 88,
what did you say?

412
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:50,600
You said you
were going somewhere.

413
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:52,333
Did you go there?

414
00:23:52,333 --> 00:23:55,233
Were you there
where Dad died?

415
00:23:58,167 --> 00:24:00,000
What were you doing there, Mom?!

416
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:06,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

417
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,100
<i> It was recorded
from a car's dash cam</i>

418
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:19,700
<i>on the day Michael Fernandez
and Federico Almazan died.</i>

419
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:21,467
<i>500 meters away
from the location.</i>

420
00:24:21,467 --> 00:24:23,367
<i> You know my loyalty
lies with you.</i>

421
00:24:23,367 --> 00:24:25,100
<i> And we're all just fishermen</i>

422
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:27,600
<i>waiting for the chance
to cap something good.</i>

423
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:31,533
<i>Why don't you just
tell the truth?!</i>

424
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:36,667
<i> Don't do anything that will
put our family at risk.</i>

425
00:24:36,667 --> 00:24:39,067
<i> And that includes Mom.</i>

